headline: Venice Film Festival: Jim Jarmusch wins top prize while Palestine dominates awards ceremony
description: The Golden Lion went to 'Father Mother Sister and Brother' by the American filmmaker on Saturday, September 6, while 'The Voice of Hind Rajab' by Tunisian director Kaouther Ben Hania, about the death of five-year-old Hind in Gaza, won the Grand Jury Prize.

headline: Louise Trotter's understated style
description: 'Essence of a Style' (6/6). Appointed to the helm of some of the biggest fashion houses, six designers are set to command the industry's attention this season.
